Week 6: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
📋 Learning Objectives
By the end of this week, you will be able to:

✅ Understand OOP concepts and principles

✅ Create classes and instantiate objects

✅ Use constructors (__init__) and destructors (__del__)

✅ Implement inheritance and method overriding

✅ Understand polymorphism and duck typing

✅ Use encapsulation with private attributes

✅ Work with special methods (__str__, __repr__, etc.)

✅ Create abstract base classes

✅ Use class methods, static methods, and properties

✅ Implement multiple inheritance and MRO

📚 Theory Content

 Types of Methods

Method Type	         |     Decorator	     |       First Parameter	   |       Called On

Instance Method	     |     None	           |       self	               |       Instance

Class Method	       |     @classmethod	   |       cls	               |       Class

Static Method	       |     @staticmethod   |     	 None	               |       Either

Property	           |     @property	     |       self	               |       Instance (as attribute)

